    "guidance": {
      "whenToUse": "Use Tabs when you need to organize related content into distinct sections within a single view, allowing users to easily switch between different panes of information without navigating away from the current context. Ideal for settings pages, data dashboards with multiple views, or product detail pages with specifications, reviews, etc.",
      "whenNotToUse": "Do NOT use Tabs for navigating to entirely different pages or sections of an application. For global navigation, use a `Navbar` or `Sidebar`. Avoid using tabs when the content for each tab is very short and could be displayed together without overwhelming the user, or when users frequently need to compare content across all sections simultaneously. Consider an `Accordion` or `Disclosure` component for less prominent, expandable content.",
      "accessibility": "Tabs should implement WAI-ARIA best practices, including `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, and `role=\"tabpanel\"`. Ensure keyboard navigation works correctly with `Tab` for focus management and arrow keys for switching between tabs within the tablist. Active tabs must have `aria-selected=\"true\"`. Associated tab panels should be linked to their respective tabs using `aria-labelledby` and `id` attributes.",
      "patterns": [
